propDescriptions.disableFocusRipple: If true, the keyboard focus ripple is disabled.
propDescriptions.disableRipple:
If true, the ripple effect is disabled.
⚠️ Without a ripple there is no styling for :focus-visible by default. Be sure to highlight the element by applying separate styles with the .Mui-focusVisible class.
propDescriptions.fullWidth: If true, the button will take up the full width of its container.
propDescriptions.href: The URL to link to when the button is clicked. If defined, an a element will be used as the root node.
propDescriptions.size: The size of the component. small is equivalent to the dense button styling.
propDescriptions.sx: The system prop that allows defining system overrides as well as additional CSS styles. See the `sx` page for more details. Warning: Use other properties instead of defining additional CSS styles if possible.
